      "Explains how to prepare count matrices and sample metadata for PyDESeq2.",
      "Guides single-factor and multi-factor differential expression designs.",
      "Shows how to run Wald tests, FDR correction, and optional LFC shrinkage.",
      "Provides a command-line script for CSV inputs, filtering, results, and plots.",
      "Helps interpret baseMean, log2FoldChange, pvalue, and padj result columns.",
      "Includes troubleshooting guidance for sample mismatches and design matrix issues."
    ],
    "limitations": [
      "It is focused on bulk RNA-seq, not single-cell differential expression workflows.",
